  "prompt": "How can apply for residency certificate in India?",
  "response": "To apply for a Residency Certificate in India, follow these general steps:\n\n1. Determine the correct authority:\n- Municipal Corporation\n- Tehsildar's office\n- District Collector's office\n- Revenue Department\n\n2. Required documents:\n- Proof of identity (Aadhaar card, Voter ID)\n- Proof of address\n- Passport-sized photographs\n- Proof of local residence (electricity bill, rental agreement)\n- Self-declaration of residence\n- Birth certificate\n- Pan Card\n- Local address proof\n\n3. Application process:\n- Obtain application form from local municipal office\n- Fill out the form completely\n- Attach all necessary documents\n- Pay required processing fees\n\n4. Submission methods:\n- In-person at designated government office\n- Online through state government websites\n- Through common service centers (CSC)\n\n5. Verification process:\n- Officials will verify submitted documents\n- Possible home verification\n- Background check\n\n6. Certificate issuance:\n- If approved, certificate will be issued\n- Typically takes 7-15 working days\n- Collect in person or receive by post\n\nNote: Specific requirements may vary slightly by state/region.",
